**Segments**

- **Type of Surgery:** The XLIF surgery market can be segmented based on the type of surgery into stand-alone XLIF surgery and hybrid XLIF surgery. Stand-alone XLIF surgery refers to the use of XLIF techniques exclusively, while hybrid XLIF surgery involves a combination of XLIF techniques with other surgical approaches.

- **End-User:** The market can also be segmented based on end-users, including hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers (ASCs), and specialized orthopedic clinics. Each end-user segment may have different requirements and preferences when it comes to XLIF surgeries.

- **Region:** Geographically, the XLIF surgery market can be segmented into North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America, and Middle East & Africa. Each region may have unique market dynamics, regulatory frameworks, and adoption rates for XLIF surgeries.

